pullRequest.body:
This is part one of #12076.

`OrzechProperty R` is a type class stating that `R` satisfies the following property: for any finitely generated `R`-module `M`, any surjective homomorphism `f : N â†’ M` from a submodule `N` of `M` to `M` is injective.

We stated some basic results about `OrzechProperty` and proved that it implies `StrongRankCondition`.

nodes.body:
Thanks for splitting the PR!

Looks good to me. If @AntoineChambert-Loir also agrees, let's get this merged.

bors d=AntoineChambert-Loir

:v: AntoineChambert-Loir can now approve this pull request. To approve and merge a pull request, simply reply with `bors r+`. More detailed instructions are available [here](https://bors.tech/documentation/getting-started/#reviewing-pull-requests).

I am not convinced about two minor points.
* the docstrings duplicate themselves and announce future work at improper places
(but they may change once the rest of the work on the Orzech property is added)
* the IBN file is short, the Orzech property is not that long, and everything is about the same kind of ideas.
So can't all of this go into a single file (IBN.lean, for example)?

> the IBN file is short, the Orzech property is not that long, and everything is about the same kind of ideas.
> So can't all of this go into a single file (IBN.lean, for example)?

I'm not sure about this, as we discussed in <https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/12076#issuecomment-2134795849> and <https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/12076#issuecomment-2135005553>. I think the reason of Orzech go to a single file is that it needs fewer imports, and maybe we can define Orzech property for modules, which, if defined, is belong to Orzech file.
good!
bors r+

Pull request successfully merged into master.

LGTM! I left some comments which expose my ignorance.
LGTM! I left some comments which expose my ignorance.
Maybe make it clear that R is a (non-commutative) ring here? I certainly see "R" and assume "commutative ring" :-/
Done.
Just to show my ignorance -- is this a quotient by a 2-sided ideal? And k<x,y> is the free non-abelian algebra?

> is this a quotient by a 2-sided ideal?

I think yes. Otherwise the quotient is not a ring.

> k<x,y> is the free non-abelian algebra?

Yes.
What is a Noetherian non-commutative ring? Is this left Noetherian, right Noetherian, or both? Sorry to be so ignorant about noncommutative rings!
It's `IsNoetherianRing`, which I think is left Noetherian, i.e. `R` itself is a Noetherian left `R`-module.
You can shorten the description in this file.
Done.
I believe this part of the docstring can be removed until these properties exist.
